    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "1. On 1 July 1947, Lt William O. McGinty, USN, 195803, P-80",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "Student, Williams Field, Chandler, Arizona, was interviewed by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "this Agent, and stated in substance: That on 30 June 1947, at about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "0910, MST, he was flying at 25,000 feet over Grand Canyon, Arizona, in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "a P-80 type aircraft. He stated that he was heading south towards Williams",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "Field, Arizona, when he saw two round objects going at inconceivable",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "speeds, straight down. He further stated that his reactions were to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "turn away from the objects. He further stated that one of the uniden-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "tifiable objects followed the other seconds apart. He further stated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "that due to the speed of the objects, he could only see that they were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "circular, and that they were possible light gray in color. He further",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "stated that in his opinion that the objects were approximately",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "eight feet in diameter. In conclusion, he stated that the objects",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "would have probably hit the ground approximately twenty-five miles",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "south of the South Rim of Grand Canyon, Arizona.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "AGENT'S NOTE: Lt McGinty gave his permanent address as N.A.M.T.C.,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Point Hagu, Port Hueneme, Calif.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "2. On 1 July 1947, Captain Malcolm G. Armstrong, O-734168,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "Instructor, Single Engine, Williams Field, Chandler, Arizona, was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "interviewed by this Agent and stated in substance: That his brother,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "1st Lt E. B. Armstrong, stationed at Hq, 10th AAF, Brooks AAF, Texas",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "had related to him that he saw a formation of unexplainable objects",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "in the vicinity of Lake Mead, Nev. Captain Armstrong, further stated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "that his brother stated the objects were heading south, and were at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "approximately 10,000 feet altitude.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "AGENT'S NOTE: Captain Armstrong could not give too much information",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "on the objects that his brother had seen. Lt. E. B. Armstrong can be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "contacted at Hq, 10th AAF, Brooks Field, Texas for further information.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
